## Ongoing & pinned
- The Order of the Silver Blade is an elite knightly order dedicated to hunting high-rank monsters and demons. They now operate under direct orders from the crown for the first time in a generation, having previously been semi-independent from the Adventurers Guild and maintaining close ties with the Church. (ongoing)
- House Bluerose is the ruling royal family of the Human Kingdom. Known for political marriages, strict expectations, and ice magic affinity. Diane, formerly the second princess, has lost her royal title and now trains as an ordinary battle-mage student. (ongoing)
- Diane Bluerose, formerly second princess of Human Kingdom, has lost her royal title and now trains as an ordinary battle-mage student at Sunspire Academy. She is a C-rank student. Her personality, skills, appearance, and other traits remain, but her occupation and royal status are changed. She no longer holds the title of princess. (ongoing)
- A fragile peace existed between the Human Kingdom, the Demon Kingdom, and various demi-human realms. However, Demon Kingdom forces have pushed past the old border markers, effectively breaking the peace. Tensions have escalated to open war. (ongoing)
- A third-year student has been missing for four days, and the Shadow Veil is rumored to be recruiting. (ongoing)
- The academy has become unusually quiet and tense since the patrol sighting. (ongoing)

## Recalled from earlier
- Ice Affinity is a specialized and potent sub-affinity of Water. It excels at freezing, area control, and elegant combat. House Bluerose has a hereditary talent for it. Diane, formerly a princess, trains rigorously to master this affinity alongside rapier techniques, now as a common battle-mage student. (ongoing)
- The Demon Kingdom rules the harsher eastern regions of Vaeldrath. Demons are masters of dark, blood, and chaos magic. The fragile peace with the Human Kingdom has been broken as Demon forces have pushed past the border markers, leading to open conflict. (ongoing)
- Demon Kingdom forces pushed past old border markers, prompting the Adventurers Guild's first S-Rank bounty in years.
- Urabel's workshop runs day and night producing healing draughts for the crown.
- The Church of the Radiant Pantheon escalates anti-demon sermons and recruits Holy Magic students before final exams.
- Alice feels growing unease about the anti-demon sermons. (ongoing)

